# Dynatrace Problem Buzzer

An enterprise-ready, background-polling notification utility designed to monitor active Dynatrace problems. The script issues real-time native desktop alerts and audibly flags newly discovered incidents without relying on bulky external UI frameworks.

---

## Features

* **Real-time Alerts:** Uses native Windows OS APIs (`MessageBoxW` and `MessageBeep`) to instantly notify engineers.
* **Production-Grade Logging:** Built-in log rotation (`RotatingFileHandler`) caps files at 5MB and keeps up to 3 backups to protect system disk space.
* **Dynamic Logging Modes:** Supports adjustments across multiple verbosity thresholds (`DEBUG`, `INFO`, `WARNING`, `ERROR`, `CRITICAL`).
* **SSL Configuration:** Enterprise networks with custom proxies or internal certificate requirements can easily toggle SSL validation via configuration.
* **Hot-Reload Architecture:** Automatically reads configuration updates at every polling cycle without needing a process restart.
* **State Persistence:** Retains tracking indices in `seen_problems.json` across process terminations to prevent duplicate notification storms.

---

## Architecture Blueprint

+-------------------------------------------------------+
|                 Windows Environment                   |
|                                                       |
|  +------------------+         +--------------------+  |
|  |   config.json    | <-----+ |   dynatracebuzzer2.1.py / EXE  |  |
|  +------------------+         +---------+----------+  |
|                                         |             |
|                                         v             |
|  +------------------+         +---------+----------+  |
|  |seen_problems.json| <-----+ |  Monitoring Cycle  |  |
|  +------------------+         +---------+----------+  |
|                                         |             |
+-----------------------------------------|-------------+
|
HTTPS (REST API)  | [SSL: True/False]
v
+-----------+-----------+
|   Dynatrace API v2    |
+-----------------------+

---

## NOTE !!!
* .exe file, config.json and seen_problems file should be in the same folder
---

## Configuration (`config.json`)

The application expects a file named `config.json` to exist in its root runtime directory.

```json
{
  "dynatrace": {
    "base_url": "https://your-tenant-id.live.dynatrace.com or https://your-managed-domain.live.dynatrace.com/e/<your managed tenant ID like this>abcd-efgh-asdf",
    "api_token": "dt0c01.XXXXXX..."
  },
  "filters": {
    "management_zones": [
      "DB",
      "DC"
    ],
    "text_filter": ""
  },
  "app_settings": {
    "log_level": "INFO",
    "ssl_verify": true,
    "interval_seconds": 60
  }
}